snippet: The Palestinian ambassador to the Czech Republic was killed Jan. 1 in an explosion at the Palestinian mission in Prague. Initial reports suggested a booby-trapped safe had exploded.
abstract: Czech police say that Jamal al-Jamal, Palestinian ambassador to the Czech Republic who was killed Jan 1 in an explosion in his new Prague residence, was probably holding an explosive device when it detonated.
lead_paragraph: The Palestinian ambassador to the Czech Republic was killed Jan. 1 in an explosion at the Palestinian mission in Prague. Initial reports suggested a booby-trapped safe had exploded.

headline.main: Palestinian Was Holding Explosive Device When He Died, Czechs Say
headline.print_headline: Czech Republic: Findings Released in Death of a Palestinian Diplomat
